        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 13 at 10:50PM CDT until August 13 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 1050 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Amherst, or 9
miles southwest of Britton, and is nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Amherst around 1055 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>Prepare immediately for large hail and deadly cloud to ground
lightning. Seek shelter inside a well-built structure. Stay away from
windows.</instruction>
